A federal judge allowed Tyco International Ltd. shareholders to proceed with a class action lawsuit, marking a significant win.
The lawsuit involves allegations of fraud and corporate looting by former executives L. Dennis Kozlowski and Mark Swartz.
Prosecutors aim to focus on the alleged thefts rather than extravagant spending.
The retrial emphasizes the executives' illegal acts, including unauthorized bonuses and stock manipulation.
Defense lawyers argue that their actions were approved by the board.
The case highlights the scrutiny of corporate scandals and the impact on workers, clients, and stockholders.
The trial underscores the importance of proving criminal intent and individual accountability.
